data.title: New York Knicks Roster
data.meta_description: New York Knicks scores, news, schedule, players, stats, rumors, depth charts and more on RealGM.com
data.text:
Landry Fields was selected as the #9 pick in the Second Round of the 2010 NBA Draft by the New York Knicks. Landry Fields signed a multi-year contract with the New York Knicks on August 24, 2010.

Andy Rautins was selected as the #8 pick in the Second Round of the 2010 NBA Draft by the New York Knicks. Andy Rautins signed a multi-year contract with the New York Knicks on August 9, 2010.

Carmelo Anthony was acquired in a trade by the New York Knicks from the Denver Nuggets on February 22, 2011.

Renaldo Balkman was acquired in a trade by the New York Knicks from the Denver Nuggets on February 22, 2011.

Chauncey Billups was acquired in a trade by the New York Knicks from the Denver Nuggets on February 22, 2011.

Anthony Carter was acquired in a trade by the New York Knicks from the Denver Nuggets on February 22, 2011.

Amar'e Stoudemire was acquired in a sign and trade by the New York Knicks from the Phoenix Suns on July 8, 2010.

Ronny Turiaf was acquired in a trade by the New York Knicks from the Golden State Warriors on July 9, 2010.

Henry Walker was acquired in a trade by the New York Knicks from the Boston Celtics on February 18, 2010.

Shelden Williams was acquired in a trade by the New York Knicks from the Denver Nuggets on February 22, 2011.
